Sentencas: The effects of anode and cathode components on solid-state reaction and sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (CGO) electrolyte were investigated in the temperature range from 900 to 1200 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication

Sentencas: The solubility limit of components in the anode was < 4 mol% for 1/2Fe2O3, < 1 mol% for NiO, and < 3 mol% for CuO.
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication

Sentencas: The solubility limit of components in the cathode was < 4 mol% for 1/2La(2)O(3), < 4 mol% for SrO, and < 1 mol% for 1/3Co(3)O(4).
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication

Sentencas: A small amount of addition of Fe2O3, Co3O4 or CuO remarkably enhanced the sintering characteristics of the CGO nanopowder.
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication

Sentencas: NiO, La2O3 or SrO addition lowered.
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication

Sentencas: In the case of the mixture of the CGO and La0.6Sr0.4CoO3, enhancement of sintering characteristics of the CGO and no reaction products were observed.
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication

Sentencas: From scanning electron microscopy observation, the sintered CGO samples with Fe2O3 showed the feature by solid-state sintering mechanism.
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication

Sentencas: For the CGO with CuO, the samples showed the trace of liquid-phase sintering.
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication

Sentencas: The samples of CGO with Co(3)O(4)included large grains, which seem to relate to cobalt vapor from the cobalt oxide particles.
Titulo: Effect of components in electrodes on sintering characteristics of Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells during fabrication
